==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Assentation
<hw>As`sen*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>assentatio</ets>. See <er>Assent</er>, v.]</ety> <def>Insincere,
flattering, or obsequious assent; hypocritical or pretended
concurrence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Abject flattery and indiscriminate <qex>assentation</qex> degrade
as much as indiscriminate contradiction and noisy debate disgust.</q>
<rj><qau>Ld. Chesterfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assentator</ent>⟦br⟧
